rComments: The course was organized by 1 midterm, 1 exam and 2 papers--for both assignments he went out of  his way to find the sources, scan them and upload to Blackboard so everyone could access them--such a nice professor. Accessible outside of class and cares about everyone doing well in his course. Don't miss lectures and you'll be fine!

Great lecturer for History. He knows his material very well. He provides all the sources needed for weekly readings AND for the essays. Course content was interesting and is willing to help all students no problem. Incredibly approachable. Only problem is that may be hard to reach to him through Office Hours so you're better off emailing him.
